        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Let's look at another case: `:4verbose !{ echo -e \"1\\2\\3\"; echo 3 >&2; exit 33; }`. We get\n```lua\n{\n  c = { { 0, ':!{ echo -e \"1\\\\2\\\\3\"; echo 3 >&2; exit 33; }\\r\\n[No write since last change]\\n', 0 } },\n  k = \"\"\n}\n{\n  c = { { 0, 'Executing command: \"{ echo -e \"1\\\\2\\\\3\"; echo 3 >&2; exit 33; }\"\\n', 0 } },\n  k = \"\"\n}\n{\n  c = { { 0, \"1\\\\2\\\\3\\n\", 0 } },\n  k = \"\"\n}\n{\n  c = { { 0, \"3\\n\", 0 } },\n  k = \"\"\n}\n{\n  c = { { 0, \"\\nshell returned 33\\n\\n\", 0 } },\n  k = \"\"\n}\n```\nIf the second (verbose) message should be passed to the `ui_attach` callback, it probably would be good to give it a different kind than for the output. I'm not sure if the message about exit code should have its own kind too. ",
